<DOC><DOCNO> AP890201-0087 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-01-89 0949EST</FILEID><FIRST>u w PM-Bush-Speech     02-01 0143</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bush-Speech,140</SECOND><HEAD>Ailing President Forced to Cancel Speech</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Bush, suffering from laryngitis,canceled a speech today before the National Association of ReligiousBroadcasters.   Bush has had a cold for about a week, and his voice has beengetting raspier and hoarser over the past several days. On Tuesday,Bush gave a speech in Norfolk, Va., and said later he had worried hewasn't going to be able to get through it. He said he had been``just croaking away.''   In announcing the cancellation of today's speech, White Housedeputy press secretary Roman Popadiuk said, ``He's feelingabsolutely superb. He has laryngitis.''   Vice President Dan Quayle addressed the broadcasters' group onMonday. Popadiuk said Bush would go through with a brief, scheduledappearance this afternoon before the National Association ofWholesale Distributors, meeting at the Old Executive Office Building.</TEXT></DOC>